# Vercel v2 (IMA camp) — always deploy summer camp after edits

After **any** code or asset change in this repo that affects the live camp site (including `index.html`, `api/`, `js/`, `vercel.json`, etc.), finish the task by running a **forced production deploy** to **`ima-summer-camp`** (`ima-summer-camp.vercel.app`). Do not skip deploy because git-push might run later; run the CLI deploy in the same session.

From **repo root** (`vercel-v2`, parent of `api/`):

```bash
cd /Users/tomrichardson/Downloads/vercel-v2 && VERCEL_ORG_ID=team_PXMrLfQ01zlse3XBsDcaPa3s VERCEL_PROJECT_ID=prj_TJxRFRbKAK4AkYBe8AKL1DoH2k9p npx vercel deploy --prod --yes
```

Retry on auth/network failure. Only skip if the user **explicitly** says not to deploy.

Note: `npx vercel --prod --yes` from this folder without those env vars may target a different linked project (`vercel-v2-alpha.vercel.app`); use the command above for summer camp.
